+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+Classification was completed before code edits and recorded in
+`artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Code and Docs Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`: normalize approval state before delegating to
+  the preview builder so fallback and live preview paths share the same
+  `human_review_required` contract.
+- `src/policy/preview.py`: preserve `approval_state` and
+  `requires_human_review` in the fallback payload instead of dropping them when
+  `preview_enabled` is false.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`: extend fallback coverage and add a regression for the
+  `manual_review` to `human_review_required` normalization case.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`: replace the stale fallback example with the
+  corrected payload and explain why downstream consumers rely on
+  `approval_state`.
+
+## Validation
+
+Ran:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result: `Ran 5 tests ... OK`
+
+## Outcome
+
+`build_policy_preview(
+    request_id="req-214",
+    approval_state="manual_review",
+    preview_enabled=False,
+    actor="review-bot",
+)`
+
+now returns a fallback payload that keeps
+`approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+`requires_human_review=true`, matching the reopened review expectation.
