+# PR-214 Reply Draft
+
+## T-214-01
+
+Addressed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`.
+The fallback payload now preserves `approval_state` and
+`requires_human_review`, and the router normalizes `manual_review` to
+`human_review_required` before building either preview shape.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. The reopened fallback regression was fixed once
+in the shared payload path rather than applying the same change twice.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This thread is outdated and points at a stale diff hunk; reviving
+legacy preview behavior would move the branch away from the current contract.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Addressed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added a regression that exercises
+`build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`
+and verifies the fallback payload keeps
+`approval_state="human_review_required"` with
+`requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Addressed in `docs/approval_policy.md`. The fallback example now shows the
+corrected payload, including `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`, and
+the notes explain why those fields remain present when preview rendering is
+unavailable.
